      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEW TARGET (4) has been superb this time in, bolting in last start in stronger company at Belmont a fortnight ago. This shapes beautifully once again from a good draw and she continues to raise the bar. Back to a CL3 here and she can continue to work through the grades. DOOR BUSTER (7) will be fitter for two trials coming into this after winning in her only run last campaign. The form out of that was strong and she looks as though she hasn't lost a yard coming into this. Can sit handy again from the draw and she can return on a strong note. SPICY THANG (5) comes here fresh and without a trial, though she is a fresh winner first-up in the past. The booking of Parnham is a good push for her chances and she'll go close if she can pick up from where she left off. NICCIMOTA (1) is better than she showed last time out and can bounce back to her best. SO IMMACULATE (6) will find this a little easier than he last start and won't be far away.",
